                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_έριστος"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">έριστος</seg></name></persName> 
                    <w lemma="δεκάτα">δε<supplied reason="lost">κάταν</supplied></w> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low"><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">τὀπόλλōνι</name></persName></supplied>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>έριστος</lem>                        
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1930"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65890"><name><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Φ</supplied>έριστος</name></persName></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="1"><lem>δε<supplied reason="lost">κάταν</supplied> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">τὀ̄πόλλο̄νι</supplied></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#oliverio1930">δε<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">κάτα</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#lazzarini1976">δε<supplied reason="lost">κάτα</supplied>ν</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>éristos <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré</supplied> la dî<supplied reason="lost">me</supplied> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">à Apollon</supplied>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>eristos <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> the ti<supplied reason="lost">the</supplied> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">to Apollo</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>eristos <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicò</supplied> come de<supplied reason="lost">cima</supplied> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ad Apollo</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The personal name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φέριστος</foreign> is not impossible but has no parallel in Cyrenaica. 
                    Anyway this word (possibly a name) being a nominative, the word 'tithe' could only be used here as an accusative, 
                    with the god's name and even with or without a verb of dedication (e.g. <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀνέθε̄κε</foreign>).</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
